                // Given a_i are non-negative integers, this case implies T must be even.
                // If T is odd, a[i] cannot be T/2.
                // So, if T is odd, a[i] == T_half (integer division) means a[i] < T/2.
                // This means a[i] would fall into the a[i] < T_half case.
                // The problem states a_i are non-negative integers.
                // So, if T is odd, a[i] == T_half is impossible.
                // Thus, this else branch is only for T_is_even and a[i] == T_half.
                // The logic for T_is_even handles it.
            }
        }
    }

