    // for A_0[j] + (sum of all d_i that affect j).
    // Let M_j_final = initial_a_plus_delta_upper_bound[j].
    // We need A_0[j] + (sum of all d_i that affect j) <= M_j_final.
    // So, A_0[j] <= M_j_final - (sum of all d_i that affect j).
    // To maximize A_0[j] while satisfying this, we set A_0[j] = M_j_final - (sum of all d_i that affect j).
    // This choice of A_0[j] ensures that A_0[j] + (sum of all d_i that affect j) = M_j_final.
    // This is the largest possible value for A_0[j] that satisfies all type 2 constraints.
    // If M_j_final was LLONG_MAX, it means no type 2 operation constrained this element.
    // In this case, we can set A_0[j] to 0 (or any value within bounds) to satisfy the constraints.
    // A_0[j] = 0 - current_delta_sum[j] would make A_0[j] + current_delta_sum[j] = 0.
