        // $M_B$ is the $(k_B+1)$-th element of $C_B$. So $C_B$ has $k_B$ elements $\le M_B$ and $k_B$ elements $\ge M_B$.
        //
        // The total number of elements $\le M_A$ is at least $k_A+1$.
        // The total number of elements $\ge M_B$ is at least $k_B+1$.
        //
        // The total number of elements in the array is $2n$.
        // The number of elements $\le M_A$ in the full sorted array is at least $k_A+1$.
        // The number of elements $\ge M_B$ in the full sorted array is at least $k_B+1$.
        //
